Standard_B2ms → 2 vCPUs, 8 GB RAM (burstable, economical)

Standard_D2_v3 → 2 vCPUs, 8 GB RAM (general purpose, Intel-based)

Standard_D2_v4 → 2 vCPUs, 8 GB RAM (general purpose, newer Intel generation)

Standard_D2_v5 → 2 vCPUs, 8 GB RAM (general purpose, latest Intel generation)

Standard_D2s_v3/v4/v5/v6 → 2 vCPUs, 8 GB RAM (same as above, but with Premium SSD support)
